I got into an accident.
What?

34:56.891 --> 34:59.527
N-Nobody's hurt, but Mike
had to come and pick me up.

34:59.527 --> 35:01.596
My God.
What happened?

35:03.497 --> 35:06.067
I had a few too many pops
with Dennis and the boys.

35:06.067 --> 35:08.269
So you were drunk?

35:08.269 --> 35:10.771
Yeah, yeah, I probably
technically still am,

35:10.771 --> 35:13.674
but I feel pretty fucking sober
right now.

35:15.810 --> 35:18.012
You like Dennis and the guys
that much that you'd be willing

35:18.012 --> 35:20.848
to, like, risk killing
someone or yourself?

35:20.848 --> 35:22.817
Because why?

35:27.154 --> 35:28.756
I didn't get it.

35:30.658 --> 35:32.927
The appointment.

35:32.927 --> 35:35.096
It's not me.

35:35.096 --> 35:38.532
The-- Wait.
How do you know?

35:39.667 --> 35:40.968
Marcella told me
this morning.

35:40.968 --> 35:43.070
Why didn't you
just come home?

35:52.346 --> 35:54.115
Yeah.
Clerk #2:
<i>Sorry to bother you, boss.</i>

35:54.115 --> 35:56.851
<i>Baker's asking or another
adjournment on the Carew case.</i>

35:56.851 --> 35:58.853
<i>Says his mother-in-law's
in the hospital.</i>

35:58.853 --> 36:01.289
Really?
He must have forgot

36:01.289 --> 36:03.557
that he told us she died
two years ago.

36:03.557 --> 36:05.993
<i>Fuck me.
I'll let the judge know.</i>

36:11.098 --> 36:13.100
Oh, Christ.

36:16.637 --> 36:19.307
So what happens now
with your job?

36:22.243 --> 36:23.744
Nothing.

36:23.744 --> 36:25.913
You crashed
a company car drunk.

36:25.913 --> 36:28.883
We know that.
And Mike knows that.

36:28.883 --> 36:31.285
But they don't know that.

36:31.285 --> 36:34.288
And they won't if they
don't have a Breathalyzer.

36:36.891 --> 36:41.595
So I'll just get lectured
for crashing a company car

36:41.595 --> 36:44.765
that they searched and seized
and didn't pay for anyway.

36:49.870 --> 36:52.606
Are you hurt anywhere?

36:52.606 --> 36:54.342
No. No, I'm okay.

36:58.212 --> 37:00.314
Fuck them.

37:00.314 --> 37:03.617
For not knowing your value.
Fuck their whole asses.

37:03.617 --> 37:06.687
Maybe when they come
crawling back in four years,
you won't be around.

37:06.687 --> 37:08.656
You could have an equity
partnership right now

37:08.656 --> 37:11.993
if you wanted one,
and Marcella knows it.

37:11.993 --> 37:14.395
I bet you some of those firms
would even get you a driver

37:14.395 --> 37:16.163
if you asked.

37:21.736 --> 37:25.039
Want to watch
something?

37:25.039 --> 37:29.043
Just space out and laugh
at people trying to ice-fish?

37:30.811 --> 37:33.247
Yeah, you do. Come on.

38:25.433 --> 38:27.735
Yeah.

38:30.204 --> 38:32.406
Good morning, sunshine!

38:32.406 --> 38:34.842
Got my guy at traffic control
out of bed last night.

38:34.842 --> 38:36.977
We towed your car
back here.
What did he say?

38:36.977 --> 38:40.448
Uh, fuck me for waking him up.
What's he supposed to say?

38:40.448 --> 38:43.084
It's not his job to give a shit
about what you all get up to.

38:43.084 --> 38:45.486
So that's it?

38:45.486 --> 38:47.922
You don't <i>want</i> that
to be it?

38:49.490 --> 38:51.392
Here's your new ride.

38:51.392 --> 38:53.294
Well, new to you,
at least.

38:53.294 --> 38:56.230
I'm not totally sure it's not
a minivan, but fingers crossed!

39:52.353 --> 39:54.054
Hey.

39:55.556 --> 39:57.291
God damn it, Conchita.

39:57.291 --> 39:58.926
You know Phillipe's
is my favorite.

39:58.926 --> 40:00.861
Why are you like this?

40:00.861 --> 40:02.329
Would you like
the other half?

40:02.329 --> 40:04.064
What do <i>you</i> think?

40:05.466 --> 40:07.168
I think you can't have it
because I'm having it later

40:07.168 --> 40:09.170
is what I'm telling myself.

40:09.170 --> 40:12.840
Hey, um, on the Badillo case,
the hearing's next week.

40:12.840 --> 40:14.475
Can you have someone call
and just make sure

40:14.475 --> 40:17.011
that the uncle
stays in town?

40:17.011 --> 40:19.046
I got a feeling I'm gonna
need him after all.

40:19.046 --> 40:21.482
Uh, yeah. I'll talk to Drea
when she's back.

40:21.482 --> 40:25.119
Great. And next time, buy me
a French dip, too, would ya?

40:25.119 --> 40:26.987
For the love of God.
I will definitely

40:26.987 --> 40:30.024
probably think about reminding
myself to remember to do that.

40:36.096 --> 40:39.400
A halfway house
in Altadena.

40:41.969 --> 40:43.938
Wow. That...

40:45.906 --> 40:47.474
It seems fast. Yeah.

40:47.474 --> 40:49.910
He said, um,
like, once they grant it,

40:49.910 --> 40:52.980
it can go fast
because of overcrowding.

40:52.980 --> 40:57.351
Like, the state being motivated
to reduce overcrowding.

40:57.351 --> 40:59.486
So what happens now?

41:00.688 --> 41:02.957
He wants to see me.

41:04.692 --> 41:08.295
And he left it up to me when.

41:08.295 --> 41:10.064
Or if.

41:13.067 --> 41:15.002
Do you want me
to see him?

41:22.710 --> 41:25.012
But that shouldn't be
why you don't.

41:29.350 --> 41:31.518
Hey, yeah, I see you.
I see you. Yes, yes.

41:31.518 --> 41:34.388
You know what?
Don't say anything yet.
I'll tell him later.

41:34.388 --> 41:36.890
I just don't want him to hear it
and to have to figure out

41:36.890 --> 41:39.360
how to be about it
in front of you.

41:41.929 --> 41:44.031
Hi!

41:44.031 --> 41:46.166
Hi, Dad!

41:46.166 --> 41:47.968
<i>At one point,
Jung had a young woman</i>

41:47.968 --> 41:50.971
<i>as a patient who believed
she lived on the moon.</i>

41:50.971 --> 41:53.007
<i>To Jung, this story
she kept telling</i>

41:53.007 --> 41:56.243
<i>about where and how she lived
was the crux of her condition.</i>

41:56.243 --> 41:59.179
<i>So he made it clear
he accepted it completely.</i>

41:59.179 --> 42:02.116
<i>And after months of analysis,</i>

42:02.116 --> 42:03.984
<i>one day, she handed him
a heavy little bag,</i>

42:03.984 --> 42:07.121
<i>and inside,
there was a loaded gun.</i>

42:07.121 --> 42:10.090
<i>"What is this?"
Jung asked the young woman.</i>

42:10.090 --> 42:13.060
<i>She told him she'd had it
with her every time they met,</i>

42:13.060 --> 42:16.430
<i>and if he ever let her down
or said he didn't believe her,</i>

42:16.430 --> 42:19.099
<i>she would have
killed him with it.</i>

42:30.511 --> 42:32.046
Hi.

42:37.351 --> 42:40.187
Did the defendant
understand the nature

42:40.187 --> 42:42.256
and the quality of his act?

42:42.256 --> 42:44.625
And at the time
that he committed it,

42:44.625 --> 42:48.529
could he distinguish
between right and wrong?

42:48.529 --> 42:50.664
Mr. Symanchuk has claimed

42:50.664 --> 42:52.633
that he couldn't,
that he didn't.

42:52.633 --> 42:54.401
He was delusional.

42:54.401 --> 42:57.604
He was under the influence
of an irresistible impulse.

42:57.604 --> 43:01.141
The legal definition of which
would mean that he was unable

43:01.141 --> 43:03.644
to conform to the requirements
of the law.

43:05.412 --> 43:07.314
Hey. I thought
you were already here.

43:07.314 --> 43:09.049
<i>I was,
but I just left.</i>

43:09.049 --> 43:12.019
<i>They found Sylvie Rubidoh's
Audi in Pacoima.</i>

43:12.019 --> 43:15.589
Holy shit. Okay.
Fingers crossed.

43:15.589 --> 43:17.424
<i>Still have a drink, though.</i>

43:17.424 --> 43:19.560
<i>I already told them
to put it on my tab.</i>

43:19.560 --> 43:22.363
<i>Remember, you're pretty fucking
good just the way you are.</i>

43:22.363 --> 43:24.031
<i>Later, tater.</i>

43:25.299 --> 43:30.571
I'm a course assistant.
It's like a T.A.

43:30.571 --> 43:32.573
I bet you're really
great at that.

43:32.573 --> 43:34.041
Why?

43:34.041 --> 43:36.143
You always had
amazing focus.

43:41.215 --> 43:43.784
Um, what's it, uh--
What's it like? The house.

43:43.784 --> 43:45.319
Crowded.

43:45.319 --> 43:48.355
But I got priority placement,
so I'm lucky.

43:48.355 --> 43:52.092
I guess just given that
I didn't have a plan.

43:57.030 --> 43:58.632
That's not true.

44:01.368 --> 44:03.437
I <i>did</i> have a plan.

44:03.437 --> 44:07.174
I just couldn't act like it was
going to happen until it did.

44:07.174 --> 44:10.577
So many years
I've missed.

44:10.577 --> 44:14.381
Which is what
I asked for.

44:14.381 --> 44:16.049
How I wanted it.

44:18.585 --> 44:21.789
Now that I'm sitting here,
I'm...

44:21.789 --> 44:24.758
I just wish I could have
all that time back.

44:26.693 --> 44:28.729
Which I know
is not reasonable.

44:31.465 --> 44:34.635
And you should know
it's okay to say no.

44:36.737 --> 44:38.205
To what?

44:41.175 --> 44:42.709
I don't know yet.

44:49.450 --> 44:52.386
But first I have to
tell you something.

44:57.257 --> 44:59.092
Hey, Dan.

45:00.594 --> 45:04.131
I thought you said you came here
a minimum three times a week.

45:04.131 --> 45:06.600
I think I said "on average,"
didn't I?

45:09.770 --> 45:11.672
I was supposed to be
meeting someone here,

45:11.672 --> 45:14.641
but he had to take off
before I arrived.

45:14.641 --> 45:17.678
He's working on a case.
He's in Investigation Bureau.

45:17.678 --> 45:20.514
So, this woman disappears
about a month ago,

45:20.514 --> 45:22.549
hasn't used her phone,
credit cards,

45:22.549 --> 45:24.218
left her passport.

45:24.218 --> 45:26.453
Her car was missing until today,
but we finally found it.

45:26.453 --> 45:27.855
And I'm not saying
I want her to be,

45:27.855 --> 45:30.390
but I hope she's in the trunk.
Right, Scanlon?

45:30.390 --> 45:31.892
I'm innocent.

45:33.560 --> 45:35.195
Meatballs
are good here.

45:35.195 --> 45:37.331
Even if they were bad,
they'd still be pretty good.

45:37.331 --> 45:39.166
That's how I feel
about meatballs.

45:39.166 --> 45:43.170
So, what if she's not?
In the trunk?

45:44.938 --> 45:47.307
Well, I've been waiting
to find the wife so I can
charge the husband,

45:47.307 --> 45:49.142
and I've been trying to find the
car so I could find the wife.

45:49.142 --> 45:50.777
So you <i>need</i> her
to be in there.

45:50.777 --> 45:53.614
Right, because your worst fear
in a case without a body is that

45:53.614 --> 45:56.483
there you are standing up
in court, middle of the trial,

45:56.483 --> 45:58.685
and then the doors fly open
and your victim walks in.

45:58.685 --> 46:00.153
<i>Are</i> you worried
about that?

46:00.153 --> 46:01.922
Are you not sure
about the husband?

46:01.922 --> 46:05.926
Does some part of you think that
the wife is gonna walk in?

46:05.926 --> 46:07.728
No. I know she isn't.

46:08.962 --> 46:10.764
I need to say this
to your face,

46:10.764 --> 46:12.799
even if you don't
believe me.

46:12.799 --> 46:14.868
I did not kill that woman.

46:17.571 --> 46:19.373
Alex Forrest. I--

46:19.373 --> 46:20.741
Yes, you did.

46:20.741 --> 46:24.244
No, Ellen. No.
No, no, no. You--

46:24.244 --> 46:26.446
<i>You</i> said that you did.
What?

46:26.446 --> 46:29.783
You lost control,
in a rage,

46:29.783 --> 46:33.887
and she didn't matter,
so then you took her life.

46:33.887 --> 46:35.722
You were there?
You asked me to come.

46:35.722 --> 46:38.792
Ellen, I didn't--
You should have tol--

46:38.792 --> 46:41.194
I didn't know that you
were going to be there.

46:41.194 --> 46:43.196
So then what would you have said
if you knew that I was?

46:43.196 --> 46:44.865
Because what I heard was
that you killed her.
That's what I heard.

46:44.865 --> 46:48.969
Ellen, I had to say that.
It's what they want to hear.

46:48.969 --> 46:50.904
If you don't say that,
then nothing else matters.

46:50.904 --> 46:52.606
Okay, so then you <i>don't</i>
think about her.

46:52.606 --> 46:54.741
I am never <i>not</i>
thinking about her

46:54.741 --> 46:57.511
unless I'm thinking
about you.

46:57.511 --> 46:59.746
And I know how all this
must sound.

47:00.914 --> 47:02.683
I did not kill her.

47:04.651 --> 47:06.253
To be free,

47:06.253 --> 47:08.622
I had to say that I did.

47:12.059 --> 47:14.461
To be here.

47:14.461 --> 47:16.897
But I am now.

47:16.897 --> 47:18.765
And I'm going to prove it.

47:20.067 --> 47:22.536
Irresistible impulses
do not lend themselves

47:22.536 --> 47:25.372
to planning, over time,
without urgency.

47:25.372 --> 47:27.874
They are not defined by having
the opportunity to act

47:27.874 --> 47:29.977
and then not doing so.

47:29.977 --> 47:33.480
Irresistible impulses
are irresistible.

49:07.526 --> 49:09.128
<i>Irresistible impulses
do not lend themselves</i>

49:09.128 --> 49:11.930
to planning over time
without urgency.

49:12.331 --> 49:14.433
The thing that's most exciting
about this show is--

49:14.433 --> 49:15.410
it's in the title.
You know what happens.
